<span id="Description"></span>
==Описание==

Выводит предопределённые переменные нагрузки лица (силы и моменты) в файл ccx_dat.

{{Version|1.0}}: Также можно выводить тепловой поток и напряжение сдвига (для последнего требуется поддержка 3D гидродинамических анализов с CalculiX, которая пока не реализована).

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
{{Version|26.3}}: Can also print electric flux in electrostatic analyses with refactored CalculiX solver. In addition to faces, edges can also be selected (they are equivalent to faces in 2D models).
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
{{Version|26.3}}: Section forces can be also printed when using the Z88 solver.
</div>

<span id="Usage"></span>
==Применение==

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
# There are several ways to invoke the command:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:FEM_ConstraintSectionPrint.svg|16px]] [[FEM_ConstraintSectionPrint|Section Print Feature]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Model → Geometrical Analysis Features → [[Image:FEM_ConstraintSectionPrint.svg|16px]] Section Print Feature}} option from the menu.
# Press the {{Button|Add}} button and select a single face ({{Version|26.3}}: or edge for 2D models) for which the output will be printed. {{Version|1.1}}: To remove entities from the selection, press the {{Button|Remove}} button.
# {{Version|1.0}}: From the ''Variable'' list, select the variable that you want to print: ''Section Force'' ({{Version|26.3}}: the only mode supported by the Z88 solver), ''Heat Flux'' or ''Drag Stress''. {{Version|26.3}}: ''Electric Flux'' is also supported.
</div>

<span id="Notes"></span>
==Примечания== 

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* The feature uses the *SECTION PRINT card in CalculiX.
</div>


